channel.title: ASF JIRA
channel.description: This file is an XML representation of an issue

item.title: [HBASE-9174] javac hangs compiling hbase-example module since namespaces went in
item.description:
javac hangs loading HRegion.class. If I remove the ns changes – the import of TableName – I can get it to compile again. Digging.

More detail to follow.
item.summary: javac hangs compiling hbase-example module since namespaces went in

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.

If I add verbose to maven-compiler-plugin, I see it is stuck loading HRegion.

After poking, it is this line that causes the hang in HRegion.java:


  0     final String logname = "hlog" + FSUtils.getTableName(tableDir) +

  1       EnvironmentEdgeManager.currentTimeMillis();

Fixes it for me.

Not sure why use of EnvironmentEdgeManager woulc cause failed load over in hbase-example module.
Just a log name. Not important. Let me run pass hadoopqa. EnvironmentEdgeManager is actually used elsewhere in HRegion.
This was on mac osx. Didn't trace it. Was stuck reading so bug in the class read in javac? Ugh
